I don't believe you people.

91
00:04:35,375 --> 00:04:37,900
Haven't we been through enough?

92
00:04:40,747 --> 00:04:43,616
Hi Corrine. It's me, Elliot.

93
00:04:43,616 --> 00:04:45,344
Do you remember?

94
00:04:47,253 --> 00:04:51,712
I almost didn't recognize you.
It's been so long. You've grown a lot.

95
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:56,127
How've you been?

96
00:04:57,964 --> 00:05:00,266
I remember you.

97
00:05:00,266 --> 00:05:02,256
You caught that man.

98
00:05:03,436 --> 00:05:05,062
Yes.

99
00:05:05,872 --> 00:05:07,600
Thank you.

100
00:05:09,742 --> 00:05:12,767
You never have to
thank me for that.

101
00:05:16,349 --> 00:05:18,918
Why aren't you at school?

102
00:05:18,918 --> 00:05:22,546
I have school here.
My mom teaches me.

103
00:05:23,056 --> 00:05:24,924
Why?

104
00:05:24,924 --> 00:05:28,261
I don't like it when
people look at me.

105
00:05:28,261 --> 00:05:30,058
I'm ugly.

106
00:05:31,864 --> 00:05:33,956
That's not true.

107
00:05:36,569 --> 00:05:39,045
Yes it is.

109
00:05:47,046 --> 00:05:48,881
It's a shame about Marchek.

110
00:05:48,881 --> 00:05:51,184
He was a good driver.
He never tried to skip his shift.

111
00:05:51,184 --> 00:05:53,486
- You know him well?
- Not to speak of.

112
00:05:53,486 --> 00:05:55,154
We drove together
a couple of times.

113
00:05:55,154 --> 00:05:58,124
- What'd you talk about?
- Usual stuff.

114
00:05:58,124 --> 00:06:00,560
Women troubles, sports...

115
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:02,929
how the union ain't
what it used to be.

116
00:06:02,929 --> 00:06:04,697
Marchek had problems
with women?

117
00:06:04,697 --> 00:06:07,567
Yeah, some ex of his
was stalking him.

118
00:06:07,567 --> 00:06:09,435
He said he had a bad break-up.

119
00:06:09,435 --> 00:06:11,938
He was with a new one
and the old one couldn't let go.

120
00:06:11,938 --> 00:06:13,691
You ever see his former lady?

121
00:06:13,691 --> 00:06:14,941
Yeah, hanging around
once or twice.

122
00:06:14,941 --> 00:06:17,944
Man, I told him to call the
cops, but he said it wasn't worth it.

123
00:06:17,944 --> 00:06:20,146
Would you recognize her
if you saw her again?

124
00:06:20,146 --> 00:06:23,516
Blonde, little over 5'.

125
00:06:23,516 --> 00:06:24,951
Drove a light blue Honda.

126
00:06:24,951 --> 00:06:26,794
She's kind of old for him, though.

127
00:06:26,794 --> 00:06:28,254
Maybe that's why
he couldn't shake her.

128
00:06:28,254 --> 00:06:30,456
Did he mention a more
recent girlfriend?

129
00:06:30,456 --> 00:06:33,760
Yeah, Gloria something.

130
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:34,961
Check with the office.

131
00:06:34,961 --> 00:06:38,197
Marchek said he didn't have family,
so she's probably his emergency notify.

132
00:06:38,197 --> 00:06:39,766
Thanks.

133
00:06:39,766 --> 00:06:42,268
Gloria, how long were you
and Thomas Marchek dating?

134
00:06:42,268 --> 00:06:43,936
About four months.

135
00:06:43,936 --> 00:06:47,240
We were already talking
about marriage, kids.

136
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:48,374
Can't this wait?

137
00:06:48,374 --> 00:06:50,843
When was the last time
you saw him?

138
00:06:50,843 --> 00:06:52,445
Night before last.

139
00:06:52,445 --> 00:06:54,847
- What about last night?
- I was working.

140
00:06:54,847 --> 00:06:57,950
- Where?
- Club Devinyl on 34th Street.

141
00:06:57,950 --> 00:06:59,485
I get off around 3:00.

142
00:06:59,485 --> 00:07:02,121
Tommy had left for work
by the time I got home.

143
00:07:02,121 --> 00:07:04,714
He ever talk about
his ex-girlfriend?

144
00:07:05,625 --> 00:07:07,293
I didn't know he had one.

145
00:07:07,293 --> 00:07:10,430
He mention anyone following
him? Maybe giving him a hard time?

146
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:14,033
Yeah, there was this one guy.
Said he was with the Citizen Watch.

147
00:07:14,033 --> 00:07:16,035
Put up flyers with Tommy's
picture on it.

148
00:07:16,035 --> 00:07:18,404
He even followed us into
a restaurant and harassed us.

149
00:07:18,404 --> 00:07:19,263
And you are?

150
00:07:19,263 --> 00:07:21,474
Louise Durning.
I am a friend of Gloria's

151
00:07:21,474 --> 00:07:24,243
And I have witnessed the abuse
they've had to endure.

152
00:07:24,243 --> 00:07:25,311
What kind of abuse?

153
00:07:25,311 --> 00:07:28,347
He called Tommy names and
called me worse for being with him.

154
00:07:28,347 --> 00:07:31,083
They couldn't go out
without being assaulted by this man...

155
00:07:31,083 --> 00:07:33,286
or one of his storm troopers.

156
00:07:33,286 --> 00:07:35,822
Nobody saw the good
in Tommy but me.

157
00:07:35,822 --> 00:07:38,187
You know what he did?

158
00:07:38,825 --> 00:07:39,959
He changed.

159
00:07:39,959 --> 00:07:42,154
It didn't bother you?

160
00:07:42,662 --> 00:07:44,363
I loved him.

161
00:07:44,363 --> 00:07:46,013
Can't you see she's in enough pain?

162
00:07:46,013 --> 00:07:48,434
Where's your compassion,
for God's sake?

163
00:07:48,434 --> 00:07:51,767
With the little girl Tommy
raped and cut.

165
00:08:01,080 --> 00:08:02,448
You got to be kidding.

166
00:08:02,448 --> 00:08:04,347
Mr. Branson, just answer the question.

167
00:08:04,347 --> 00:08:06,419
I was in Chicago on business.

168
00:08:06,419 --> 00:08:07,634
You want the receipts?
I can prove it.

169
00:08:07,634 --> 00:08:09,222
No, that won't be necessary.

170
00:08:09,222 --> 00:08:10,556
Actually, it is.

171
00:08:10,556 --> 00:08:12,058
You of all people.

172
00:08:12,058 --> 00:08:15,322
Trust me, I don't like this
any better than you do.

173
00:08:16,329 --> 00:08:18,498
Thank you.

174
00:08:18,498 --> 00:08:22,263
- You talk to Lindsay, Corrine?
- Yes.

175
00:08:22,969 --> 00:08:24,136
How're they doing?

176
00:08:24,136 --> 00:08:26,706
Your daughter seems lonely.
Do you get to see her often?

177
00:08:26,706 --> 00:08:28,941
Not as often as I should.

178
00:08:28,941 --> 00:08:30,843
I can't take Lindsay
blaming me anymore.

179
00:08:30,843 --> 00:08:33,334
Josh, it's not your fault.

180
00:08:35,448 --> 00:08:38,749
When that monster Marchek
raped my little girl,

181
00:08:38,749 --> 00:08:40,653
he killed a part of me.

182
00:08:40,653 --> 00:08:43,022
Your daughter is
still alive...

183
00:08:43,022 --> 00:08:44,924
and she misses you very much.

184
00:08:44,924 --> 00:08:46,959
Her mother won't let me near her.

185
00:08:46,959 --> 00:08:49,095
She says they don't get
out very often.

186
00:08:49,095 --> 00:08:51,460
She shut herself off.

187
00:08:53,299 --> 00:08:56,580
I've tried to talk to her.
I even bought her a car,

188
00:08:56,580 --> 00:08:59,672
hoping she'd take Corrine to
the country where she can...

189
00:08:59,672 --> 00:09:02,640
play outside and feel safe.

190
00:09:03,242 --> 00:09:06,040
- What kind of car?
- An Accord.

191
00:09:06,746 --> 00:09:08,440
Why?

192
00:09:09,248 --> 00:09:12,485
Does Lindsay take Corrine with
her when she goes out to run errands?

193
00:09:12,485 --> 00:09:16,155
No, the neighbor across
the hall stays with her.

194
00:09:16,155 --> 00:09:19,492
A sweet lady
named Virginia Koehler.

195
00:09:19,492 --> 00:09:21,160
You think Lindsay
killed the bastard?

196
00:09:21,160 --> 00:09:23,763
We don't think anything,
Mrs. Koehler. We're talking to everyone.

197
00:09:23,763 --> 00:09:26,299
You take care of Corrine when
her mother is out. Is that correct?

198
00:09:26,299 --> 00:09:28,734
I'm one of the only people
she trusts.

199
00:09:28,734 --> 00:09:31,270
After the terrible thing that happened,
she's very careful.

200
00:09:31,270 --> 00:09:33,506
- You baby-sit Corrine last night?
- Why?

201
00:09:33,506 --> 00:09:36,442
Mrs. Koehler, do you think Lindsay
murdered her daughter's attacker?

202
00:09:36,442 --> 00:09:38,678
- No.
- Then tell us the truth.

203
00:09:38,678 --> 00:09:41,738
Did you stay with Corrine
last night?

204
00:09:44,450 --> 00:09:46,586
Yes.

205
00:09:46,586 --> 00:09:48,254
Lindsay went to the
grocery store.

206
00:09:48,254 --> 00:09:50,523
And what time did she return?

207
00:09:50,523 --> 00:09:52,513
About 11:00.

208
00:09:53,492 --> 00:09:55,895
She's all that little girl has.

209
00:09:55,895 --> 00:09:58,260
Please leave her alone.

210
00:10:01,434 --> 00:10:05,237
The DMV lists Lindsay Branson
as the owner of a '98 blue Honda Accord.

211
00:10:05,237 --> 00:10:06,706
No tickets. No warrants.

212
00:10:06,706 --> 00:10:08,140
Any registered weapons?

213
00:10:08,140 --> 00:10:11,014
A Smith and Wesson 9mm
registered to Josh Branson,

214
00:10:11,014 --> 00:10:13,312
but not to the ex-wife.

215
00:10:13,312 --> 00:10:14,143
Pick her up.

216
00:10:14,143 --> 00:10:16,148
Okay, why are we doing this, now?

217
00:10:16,148 --> 00:10:18,165
The gun is registered to
the husband.

218
00:10:18,165 --> 00:10:20,152
They're divorced.
They live apart.

219
00:10:20,152 --> 00:10:21,754
I want her in a line-up.

220
00:10:21,754 --> 00:10:24,205
If Marchek's co-worker can ID
Mrs. Branson as the stalker,

221
00:10:24,205 --> 00:10:25,491
then we'll play it out.

222
00:10:25,491 --> 00:10:27,293
This is based on
circumstantial evidence.

223
00:10:27,293 --> 00:10:29,395
We've twisted suspects
in the wind for a lot less...

224
00:10:29,395 --> 00:10:30,896
than what we've got on
paper right now.

225
00:10:30,896 --> 00:10:32,798
Those suspects...

226
00:10:32,798 --> 00:10:36,369
didn't have a daughter who
was raped and had her face sliced up.

227
00:10:36,369 --> 00:10:38,471
She clears the line-up,
she goes home.

228
00:10:38,471 --> 00:10:39,672
I'm not doing this.

229
00:10:39,672 --> 00:10:41,540
- Elliot.
- No. You know something...

230
00:10:41,540 --> 00:10:44,276
this woman's already
living in hell.

231
00:10:44,276 --> 00:10:48,047
And now you're asking me
to drag her in like a criminal.

232
00:10:48,047 --> 00:10:50,349
- I'm not doing it.
- This isn't your call, Detective.

233
00:10:50,349 --> 00:10:53,319
Counselor, you know something,
I don't answer to you.

234
00:10:53,319 --> 00:10:55,588
You answer to me.

235
00:10:55,588 --> 00:10:57,502
And I suggest you adjust
your attitude before

236
00:10:57,502 --> 00:11:00,422
I write you up on insubordination.

237
00:11:09,669 --> 00:11:11,491
I just don't think 
we have enough evidence.

238
00:11:11,491 --> 00:11:13,205
I say we do.

239
00:11:13,205 --> 00:11:15,798
Either get right with that 
or go home.

240
00:11:33,392 --> 00:11:37,596
Can you identify the woman who was
following Tommy Marchek?

241
00:11:37,596 --> 00:11:39,198
Number three. That's her.

242
00:11:39,198 --> 00:11:40,800
Take your time.

243
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:43,202
What for? It's number three.

244
00:11:43,202 --> 00:11:46,105
Can I go now? I got a lot
of deliveries to get out.

245
00:11:46,105 --> 00:11:47,697
Yeah.

246
00:11:49,742 --> 00:11:52,144
Search warrants were issued
for the premises and the car?

247
00:11:52,144 --> 00:11:53,913
Munch and Fin are on it.

248
00:11:53,913 --> 00:11:55,915
Are you gonna be able to
do the interrogation...

249
00:11:55,915 --> 00:11:58,117
or do I need to get
another set of detectives?

250
00:11:58,117 --> 00:12:00,244
It's not a problem.

251
00:12:06,792 --> 00:12:08,794
Can I get you anything?

252
