- No, it was quick.

293
00:14:44,950 --> 00:14:48,010
But not quick enough, 
right, Detective?

294
00:14:49,655 --> 00:14:52,157
Your son was murdered.

295
00:14:52,157 --> 00:14:54,493
We're trying to find out who did it.

296
00:14:54,493 --> 00:14:57,291
- What do you care?
- It's our job.

297
00:14:58,097 --> 00:14:59,531
And my cross to bear.

298
00:14:59,531 --> 00:15:03,168
- Mrs. Moss, this isn't about you.
- No?

299
00:15:03,168 --> 00:15:07,331
If my son hadn't been born,
those two women never would've been raped.

300
00:15:07,873 --> 00:15:11,672
I ask myself what I did wrong
and have no answers.

301
00:15:13,812 --> 00:15:18,450
Did your son mention anything about
having trouble with anyone lately?

302
00:15:18,450 --> 00:15:22,087
There were sex offender flyers
all over the neighborhood...

303
00:15:22,087 --> 00:15:25,124
obscenities spray-painted 
on my door and...

304
00:15:25,124 --> 00:15:27,593
the man who beat him 
to a pulp last week.

305
00:15:27,593 --> 00:15:29,561
Did your son tell you 
who this man was?

306
00:15:29,561 --> 00:15:31,664
No, but I can guess.

307
00:15:31,664 --> 00:15:34,934
The owner of the corner market, Pulham.

308
00:15:34,934 --> 00:15:36,936
He hated Craig.

309
00:15:36,936 --> 00:15:40,337
Had half-a-dozen flyers
pasted in the store window.

310
00:15:41,006 --> 00:15:43,542
I hated what he did...

311
00:15:43,542 --> 00:15:45,634
but I loved my son.

312
00:15:46,178 --> 00:15:47,975
