we'll escort your family back home.

501
00:24:11,716 --> 00:24:13,985
No, thanks, Detective...

502
00:24:13,985 --> 00:24:16,350
they're safer where they are.

503
00:24:21,159 --> 00:24:24,496
I worked at the shop until 10:00.
Then I went home.

504
00:24:24,496 --> 00:24:26,465
- You go out for dinner break?
- About 6:00.

505
00:24:26,465 --> 00:24:28,433
Where'd you go?

506
00:24:28,433 --> 00:24:29,701
For a walk.

507
00:24:29,701 --> 00:24:33,104
James Campbell said that you wound up
at his place, threatened his life.

508
00:24:33,104 --> 00:24:35,674
I tried to save his neck,
but he wouldn't listen.

509
00:24:35,674 --> 00:24:39,044
Instead he gets in my face, 
calls me a stalker.

510
00:24:39,044 --> 00:24:42,881
I don't have to take that from anyone,
least of all a stinking rapist.

511
00:24:42,881 --> 00:24:45,406
That why you took a shot at him?

512
00:24:46,251 --> 00:24:48,086
I didn't shoot at anybody.

513
00:24:48,086 --> 00:24:49,821
He saw you outside his window.

514
00:24:49,821 --> 00:24:53,859
He was mistaken. 
Like I said, I was at work.

515
00:24:53,859 --> 00:24:55,727
Anybody with you?

516
00:24:55,727 --> 00:24:57,922
My partner Paul Cormick.

517
00:25:00,632 --> 00:25:03,535
We're rebuilding an engine,
the block is cracked.

518
00:25:03,535 --> 00:25:05,437
How many guns do you own?

519
00:25:05,437 --> 00:25:08,674
Five...
counting the engraved Marine Dragoon.

520
00:25:08,674 --> 00:25:10,408
But you already know that, don't you?

521
00:25:10,408 --> 00:25:11,776
You expecting a war?

522
00:25:11,776 --> 00:25:15,575
I shoot competitively.
But you know that, too.

523
00:25:17,182 --> 00:25:19,284
Tell you what...

524
00:25:19,284 --> 00:25:22,521
why don't the two of you
tell me what you want...

525
00:25:22,521 --> 00:25:25,457
and I'll tell you
if I'm gonna make it easy...

526
00:25:25,457 --> 00:25:26,725
or I'm gonna make it hard.

527
00:25:26,725 --> 00:25:28,960
- Give up your 9mm for testing.
- No.

528
00:25:28,960 --> 00:25:32,097
Then why do we have to go through this, then?

529
00:25:32,097 --> 00:25:34,533
You gonna play us,
we'll just keep right on digging.

530
00:25:34,533 --> 00:25:36,401
Then grab a shovel, brother.

531
00:25:36,401 --> 00:25:40,071
No probable cause, no warrant, no guns.

532
00:25:40,071 --> 00:25:42,240
We know that you followed these guys.

533
00:25:42,240 --> 00:25:45,410
And no one filed a complaint,
so what's the problem?

534
00:25:45,410 --> 00:25:47,779
The problem is anyone
you don't like, they wind up dead.

535
00:25:47,779 --> 00:25:50,382
Pedophiles and rapists.

536
00:25:50,382 --> 00:25:52,315
Don't waste your pity.

537
00:25:54,319 --> 00:25:57,549
You used to be a good cop, 
what happened?

538
00:26:03,361 --> 00:26:06,694
Are you guys gonna charge me 
with anything?

539
00:26:07,832 --> 00:26:10,095
Or can I go home now?

540
00:26:12,404 --> 00:26:14,205
That was Munch.

541
00:26:14,205 --> 00:26:17,742
Cormick's wife puts her husband
at home by 9:00 pm.

542
00:26:17,742 --> 00:26:19,978
Well, there goes Winfield's alibi.

543
00:26:19,978 --> 00:26:22,380
We'll need warrants to cover
the garage and home.

544
00:26:22,380 --> 00:26:24,507
Cabot's already on it.

545
00:26:25,216 --> 00:26:27,218
Take a look at this.

546
00:26:27,218 --> 00:26:29,588
I called Winfield's captain in Albany.

547
00:26:29,588 --> 00:26:32,791
Got the off-the-record on his bad shoot.

548
00:26:32,791 --> 00:26:36,094
Turns out the gun the perp
was carrying had no prints.

549
00:26:36,094 --> 00:26:37,195
It was a drop?

550
00:26:37,195 --> 00:26:39,097
Serial number was filed clean.

551
00:26:39,097 --> 00:26:42,467
Winfield had eight commendations
up to that point?

552
00:26:42,467 --> 00:26:45,704
That's why they offered
him early retirement.

553
00:26:45,704 --> 00:26:48,073
The case he was working on 
was real bad ass.

554
00:26:48,073 --> 00:26:50,700
Captain said it ate him to the bone.

555
00:26:51,242 --> 00:26:53,144
The warrants are on the way.

556
00:26:53,144 --> 00:26:55,146
I already sent Munch and Fin 
to the residence.

557
00:26:55,146 --> 00:26:58,738
You two go to the business.
The unis'll meet you there.

559
00:27:05,323 --> 00:27:06,758
What the hell is this?

560
00:27:06,758 --> 00:27:09,556
Sorry, Sam. I couldn't stop them.

561
00:27:19,704 --> 00:27:21,539
So much for professional courtesy.

562
00:27:21,539 --> 00:27:22,907
You brought this on yourself.

563
00:27:22,907 --> 00:27:25,644
Just another day on
the thin blue line, Detective?

564
00:27:25,644 --> 00:27:26,978
- You better watch out.
- Yeah.

565
00:27:26,978 --> 00:27:28,480
Or you'll wind up just like me.

566
00:27:28,480 --> 00:27:29,748
Well, thanks for the advice.

567
00:27:29,748 --> 00:27:32,550
Just let us do our job and
we'll be out of your hair.

568
00:27:34,319 --> 00:27:36,955
- You all right?
- Yep.

569
00:27:36,955 --> 00:27:38,089
I'll get the first-aid kit.

570
00:27:38,089 --> 00:27:42,218
Detectives, found this
in an oil drum out back.

571
00:27:43,228 --> 00:27:46,798
Mr. Winfield, I won't forget
about that first aid kit.

572
00:27:46,798 --> 00:27:50,068
You're under arrest for the murder
of Thomas Marchek and Craig Moss...

573
00:27:50,068 --> 00:27:52,137
and the attempted murder of James Campbell.

574
00:27:52,137 --> 00:27:54,939
- You have the right to remain silent.
- I know my rights.

575
00:27:54,939 --> 00:27:57,430
Well, then, let's get out of here.

576
00:27:59,044 --> 00:28:01,746
Ballistics report came back
positive for the Campbell attack.

577
00:28:01,746 --> 00:28:03,248
But it's no match on the murders.

578
00:28:03,248 --> 00:28:04,783
- You sure?
- Tested it twice.

579
00:28:04,783 --> 00:28:06,151
We don't have the murder weapon.

580
00:28:06,151 --> 00:28:07,352
Then we don't have a case.

581
00:28:07,352 --> 00:28:10,188
The most I can charge him with is
attempted murder on Mr. Campbell.

582
00:28:10,188 --> 00:28:12,524
- Unless you play hardball.
- What are you suggesting?

583
00:28:12,524 --> 00:28:15,827
You could threaten to kick up enough
dust to re-open the Albany investigation.

584
00:28:15,827 --> 00:28:18,363
Look, wait a minute, I read the file.

585
00:28:18,363 --> 00:28:21,099
There was a kid in the car and
he thought the perp was carrying.

586
00:28:21,099 --> 00:28:23,501
The skell had already raped
and tortured the kid's mother.

587
00:28:23,501 --> 00:28:26,104
I know the facts. But we've
got two murders to close.

588
00:28:26,104 --> 00:28:29,140
So we pad our win column
at the expense of a good cop...

589
00:28:29,140 --> 00:28:30,475
because he made a judgment call?

590
00:28:30,475 --> 00:28:33,611
If he killed those men, I don't give a damn
how many commendations he had.

591
00:28:33,611 --> 00:28:35,513
He's a murderer and 
we're going to nail his ass.

592
00:28:35,513 --> 00:28:37,503
Now do you have a problem with that?

593
00:28:38,116 --> 00:28:40,045
- All I'm saying...
- What?

594
00:28:40,045 --> 00:28:42,245
What are you saying, Detective?

595
00:28:43,288 --> 00:28:46,024
I think I understand him.

596
00:28:46,024 --> 00:28:49,015
And I'm asking for a shot at him.

597
00:29:03,575 --> 00:29:05,838
You know, these rooms 
all look the same.

598
00:29:06,377 --> 00:29:08,847
They've got one up in Albany with
a window just like this one.

599
00:29:08,847 --> 00:29:11,542
Same rusty gratings, same size.

600
00:29:12,350 --> 00:29:14,419
Rooms even smell the same.

601
00:29:14,419 --> 00:29:16,921
- How long on the job?
- Sixteen years.

602
00:29:16,921 --> 00:29:19,855
Solid, from what I hear.

603
00:29:20,725 --> 00:29:23,125
I was on my way to being Captain.

604
00:29:25,196 --> 00:29:27,664
Then Alan Cryter came along.

605
00:29:30,268 --> 00:29:32,531
I had my own Alan Cryter.

606
00:29:33,338 --> 00:29:38,443
Insurance salesman. Ran his business
out of a converted garage in Queens.

607
00:29:38,443 --> 00:29:43,581
Well liked. Would invite the neighborhood
kids up for ice cream and stories.

608
00:29:43,581 --> 00:29:47,018
One day, a six-year-old girl goes missing...

609
00:29:47,018 --> 00:29:50,155
from a playground in Soho.

610
00:29:50,155 --> 00:29:52,090
Actually...

611
00:29:52,090 --> 00:29:55,126
long story short, we find her...

612
00:29:55,126 --> 00:29:59,664
underneath the floorboards of his office,
along with three other children.

613
00:29:59,664 --> 00:30:03,234
All of them in various stages 
of decomposition.

614
00:30:03,234 --> 00:30:07,305
But he is gone, and I'm left...

615
00:30:07,305 --> 00:30:09,170
with a cold case.

616
00:30:09,741 --> 00:30:16,677
And two years nothing but silence...
and headaches.

617
00:30:18,449 --> 00:30:20,685
I developed these debilitating headaches.

618
00:30:20,685 --> 00:30:22,787
I wasn't sleeping a lot.

619
00:30:22,787 --> 00:30:26,524
I kept having these recurring nightmares...

620
00:30:26,524 --> 00:30:29,093
where my own children would be
underneath these floorboards...

621
00:30:29,093 --> 00:30:31,618
that I couldn't pry up.

622
00:30:32,931 --> 00:30:38,130
And then one day I'm just gassing up
my car in Chelsea and there he is.

623
00:30:38,636 --> 00:30:41,773
And before I know it I've got his face...

624
00:30:41,773 --> 00:30:45,910
sandwiched between his windshield
and the muzzle of my gun.

625
00:30:45,910 --> 00:30:49,004
And I'm yelling, "Freeze."

626
00:30:49,747 --> 00:30:53,952
And I realize that I'm yelling at myself.

627
00:30:53,952 --> 00:30:57,622
Because I can't stop my finger
from pulling the trigger.

628
00:30:57,622 --> 00:31:01,326
And I'm praying for him to blink.
I'm praying for him to twitch.

629
00:31:01,326 --> 00:31:05,830
Just do something to give me an excuse.

630
00:31:05,830 --> 00:31:09,128
And then I see a face inside of his car.

631
00:31:10,635 --> 00:31:12,124
It's...

632
00:31:13,771 --> 00:31:17,809
a girl, this beautiful,
little six-year-old girl...

633
00:31:17,809 --> 00:31:20,470
these big eyes.

634
00:31:24,716 --> 00:31:27,207
I figured she'd seen enough.

635
00:31:30,221 --> 00:31:32,712
Yeah, she'd seen enough.

636
00:31:36,961 --> 00:31:39,361
Your headaches go away?

637
00:31:40,732 --> 00:31:42,392
Yeah.

638
00:31:44,202 --> 00:31:47,227
It's the only difference between us.

639
00:31:51,576 --> 00:31:54,245
I didn't see the kid's eyes.

640
00:31:54,245 --> 00:31:58,681
The perp pulled him from the car
and used him as a shield.

641
00:32:00,585 --> 00:32:03,121
After what the loser had done
to the mother and the sister...

642
00:32:03,121 --> 00:32:05,189
I had no doubts what he'd do with the boy.

643
00:32:05,189 --> 00:32:09,591
Anyway, the boy bit him and ran. I shot.

644
00:32:12,497 --> 00:32:16,301
I could have sworn 
that son of a bitch had a gun.

645
00:32:16,301 --> 00:32:18,098
But maybe...

646
00:32:19,938 --> 00:32:22,030
it was just wishful thinking.

647
00:32:36,721 --> 00:32:39,280
We've got to do the right thing here.

648
00:32:48,066 --> 00:32:50,329
I didn't kill those men.

649
00:32:51,336 --> 00:32:54,973
I handed out flyers to inform
and prevent. That's all.

650
00:32:54,973 --> 00:32:56,541
James Campbell?

651
00:32:56,541 --> 00:32:58,309
James Campbell was next on the list.

652
00:32:58,309 --> 00:33:02,677
I figured if I scared him off,
at least he'd be alive.

653
00:33:04,682 --> 00:33:06,809
Anything else you can tell me?

654
00:33:12,023 --> 00:33:15,458
On the night of Marchek's murder,
I was on duty.

655
00:33:15,960 --> 00:33:19,597
I heard the shots.
I ran towards the sound.

656
00:33:19,597 --> 00:33:24,836
When I got there, I saw a woman
fleeing the crime scene.

657
00:33:24,836 --> 00:33:26,701
Description?

658
00:33:29,040 --> 00:33:32,710
5'6", brown hair, 120-ish lbs.

659
00:33:32,710 --> 00:33:37,248
Black leather jacket, flapping open,
blue sequined top, dark pants...

660
00:33:37,248 --> 00:33:38,908
boots.

661
00:33:44,255 --> 00:33:47,087
Why didn't you tell us this before?

662
00:33:48,826 --> 00:33:53,126
When I saw it was Marchek,
I figured he got what he deserved.

663
00:34:01,139 --> 00:34:04,301
Can you do me any favors on this?

664
00:34:10,515 --> 00:34:12,884
Gloria's not here, Detective.
She's off today.

665
00:34:12,884 --> 00:34:15,553
- But she was on Thursday.
- Yeah. Why?

666
00:34:15,553 --> 00:34:17,922
Her time card said she worked till 3:00 am.

667
00:34:17,922 --> 00:34:20,324
- So?
- She work the whole night?

668
00:34:20,324 --> 00:34:21,392
Must've.

669
00:34:21,392 --> 00:34:22,849
How well did you know her boyfriend?

670
00:34:22,849 --> 00:34:25,296
Not very well.
She said he was nice.

671
00:34:25,296 --> 00:34:27,698
Which she deserved after
the long line of scuzzballs...

672
00:34:27,698 --> 00:34:30,168
who mooched her money
and beat the crap out of her.

673
00:34:30,168 --> 00:34:31,836
It was sad when they broke up.

674
00:34:31,836 --> 00:34:34,005
Broke up? When did that happen?

675
00:34:34,005 --> 00:34:37,008
About a week ago.
Glo took it hard.

676
00:34:37,008 --> 00:34:38,743
I think she still loved him.

677
00:34:38,743 --> 00:34:41,446
Missed a lot of work.
Almost got canned.

678
00:34:41,446 --> 00:34:43,915
But she worked until 3:00 last Thursday?

679
00:34:43,915 --> 00:34:45,750
You checked her time card.

680
00:34:45,750 --> 00:34:47,952
We have a witness that says otherwise.

681
00:34:47,952 --> 00:34:50,588
Unless you want to be charged
as accessory to murder,

682
00:34:50,588 --> 00:34:53,488
I suggest you tell us the truth.

683
00:34:56,694 --> 00:34:59,230
Gloria ducked out about 11:00.

684
00:34:59,230 --> 00:35:00,965
- Where'd she go?
- I don't know.

685
00:35:00,965 --> 00:35:03,835
- Did she come back?
- No.

686
00:35:03,835 --> 00:35:07,071
Manager didn't miss her, so
I punched her card when I left.

687
00:35:07,071 --> 00:35:10,875
- Did she work night before last?
- It was her night off.

688
00:35:10,875 --> 00:35:13,411
Look, I know Gloria.

689
00:35:13,411 --> 00:35:16,747
She's a little messed up,
but she's a sweet girl.

690
00:35:16,747 --> 00:35:19,044
She wouldn't hurt anybody.

691
00:35:19,750 --> 00:35:23,020
You sure about that?
Okay, John, thanks a lot.

692
00:35:23,020 --> 00:35:25,189
Seems Gloria's alibi just went south.

693
00:35:25,189 --> 00:35:26,747
Here it is.

694
00:35:28,993 --> 00:35:30,661
Gloria!

695
00:35:30,661 --> 00:35:34,332
Detectives Benson and Stabler.
We spoke this morning.

696
00:35:34,332 --> 00:35:35,833
Wow.

697
00:35:35,833 --> 00:35:40,037
She said that she'd be here,
as if she could really hear me.

698
00:35:40,037 --> 00:35:41,172
Gloria?

699
00:35:41,172 --> 00:35:44,275
Damn inconsiderate.
Did you get any answer?

700
00:35:44,275 --> 00:35:45,443
And who are you?

701
00:35:45,443 --> 00:35:49,280
Earl Zito, I live below in 2-C.
Listen to that.

702
00:35:49,280 --> 00:35:51,782
- How long's this been going on?
- Over an hour.

703
00:35:51,782 --> 00:35:55,052
Yeah, I called the super,
but you know, it's...

704
00:35:55,052 --> 00:35:57,188
Stay there please.

705
00:35:57,188 --> 00:35:59,656
I hope the deadbolt isn't on.

706
00:36:08,566 --> 00:36:10,260
Olivia!

707
00:36:13,171 --> 00:36:17,008
Call for a wagon. I got a pulse here.
Very faint.

708
00:36:17,008 --> 00:36:19,840
2414 to central. 2414 to central.

709
00:36:20,344 --> 00:36:22,680
Got a 10-54 attempted suicide...

710
00:36:22,680 --> 00:36:25,883
at 28 Lexington Avenue and 26th Street.

711
00:36:25,883 --> 00:36:27,285
Put a rush on the bus.

712
00:36:27,285 --> 00:36:29,086
Grab another towel.
I'm making a tourniquet.

714
00:36:33,491 --> 00:36:35,026
Can you tie the other one for me?

715
00:36:35,026 --> 00:36:38,563
We need to get her downstairs.
Gloria, can you hear me?

716
00:36:38,563 --> 00:36:40,553
Stay with me.

717
00:36:42,200 --> 00:36:43,601
She's a lucky young woman...

718
00:36:43,601 --> 00:36:46,537
another minute or two and
she would've bled to death.

719
00:36:46,537 --> 00:36:48,472
Can we talk to her now?

720
00:36:48,472 --> 00:36:53,544
Before you do, I need to inform you
about your potential exposure.

721
00:36:53,544 --> 00:36:55,479
To what?

722
00:36:55,479 --> 00:36:58,152
The paramedics found Viracept,
a protease inhibitor,

723
00:36:58,152 --> 00:36:59,817
in Gloria's medicine cabinet.

724
00:36:59,817 --> 00:37:03,287
She confirmed that she's HIV-positive.

725
00:37:03,287 --> 00:37:06,457
Since there was a lot of blood 
at the scene...

726
00:37:06,457 --> 00:37:10,461
- Elliot.
- Okay, Doc. Thanks for the heads-up.

727
00:37:10,461 --> 00:37:13,764
We should talk to Gloria
while she's still awake.

728
00:37:16,601 --> 00:37:18,836
You should've just let me die.

729
00:37:18,836 --> 00:37:20,538
That's not an answer.

730
00:37:20,538 --> 00:37:23,040
How do you know?

731
00:37:23,040 --> 00:37:25,943
Did you hurt yourself
because of Tommy Marchek?

732
00:37:25,943 --> 00:37:27,511
Yes.

733
00:37:27,511 --> 00:37:29,747
Because he broke up with you?

734
00:37:29,747 --> 00:37:30,982
I broke up with him.

735
00:37:30,982 --> 00:37:35,653
- Why?
- Son of a bitch gave me HIV.

736
00:37:35,653 --> 00:37:37,788
Is that why you killed him?

737
00:37:37,788 --> 00:37:39,653
Isn't that enough?

738
00:37:40,458 --> 00:37:42,084
And Moss?

739
00:37:43,861 --> 00:37:45,229
Who?

740
00:37:45,229 --> 00:37:47,060
Craig Moss.

741
00:37:49,500 --> 00:37:51,592
I killed him, too.

742
00:37:54,839 --> 00:37:57,899
- Why'd you use a knife on him?
- What do you care?

743
00:37:58,643 --> 00:38:01,543
He's dead. I did it.

744
00:38:02,246 --> 00:38:04,213
Now leave me alone.

745
00:38:11,489 --> 00:38:13,324
She's lying. She's protecting someone.

746
00:38:13,324 --> 00:38:15,293
The question is, who?

747
00:38:15,293 --> 00:38:18,696
We still haven't found any connection
between Gloria and Moss.

748
00:38:18,696 --> 00:38:20,798
I don't even think she knew the guy.

749
00:38:20,798 --> 00:38:23,668
Hold on. Wait a minute.

